  <thing id="pwBotWCust" name="Body of the Wolf" description="{b}Effect:{/b} You change from your humanoid form to the form of a wolf, or vice versa. When you change from wolf form to humanoid form, you can shift 1 square.\n    While in wolf form, you retain your normal game statistics and size, but gain a +1 bonus to speed. Your equipment becomes part of your wolf form. You continue to gain the benefits of the equipment you wear, except shields and item powers. While equipment is part of your wolf form, it cannot be removed, and anything in a container that is part of your wolf form is inaccessible.\n    You gain proficiency with your bite while in wolf form. Treat your bite as a melee weapon with a +3 proficiency bonus, a 1d8 damage die, and the enhancement bonus of your primary weapon." compset="Power">
